ortfolio-iran-war-oil-prices-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIran-war-driven%20chaos%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20pillar%20that%20bulls%20have%20been%20able%20to%20lean%20on%20is%20the%20resiliency%20of%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20pillar%20might%20be%20starting%20to%20wobble%2C%20however%2C%20according%20to%20Soci%C3%A9t%C3%A9%20G%C3%A9n%C3%A9rale%20strategist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-albert-edwards-bubble-bearish-outlook-japan-yields-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAlbert%20Edwards%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForward%2012-month%20profit%20estimates%2C%20which%20tend%20to%20be%20the%20primary%20driver%20of%20stock%20performance%2C%20were%20revised%20up%20again%20in%20March%20for%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500.%20The%20rosy%20outlook%20for%20earnings%20has%20provided%20solace%20to%20investors%20recently%20%E2%80%94%20despite%20gas%20prices%20threatening%20to%20fuel%20both%20inflation%20and%20a%20pullback%20in%20growth%2C%20the%20cold%2C%20hard%20earnings%20numbers%20have%20been%20steadfast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Edwards%2C%20a%20self-styled%20uber-bear%20who%20called%20the%202000%20and%202008%20crashes%2C%20said%20in%20a%20note%20to%20clients%20on%20Thursday%20that%20this%20could%20be%20lulling%20investors%20to%20sleep%2C%20and%20they%20could%20be%20in%20for%20a%20rude%20awakening%20in%20the%20months%20ahead%20as%20earnings%20eventually%20start%20to%20roll%20over%20thanks%20to%20elevated%20oil%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20equity%20market%20may%20be%20looking%20in%20the%20rear-view%20earnings%20mirror%20and%20taking%20comfort%20from%20such%20robust%20profits%20growth%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20Tech%2FAI-related%20sectors%2C%26quot%3B%20Edwards%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20metric%20underpinning%20Edwards'%20argument%20is%20the%20growth%20of%20optimism%20in%20analyst%20earnings%20upgrades.%20While%20optimism%20is%20still%20rising%2C%20the%20pace%20of%20that%20growth%20appears%20to%20have%20topped%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20black%20dotted%20lines%20in%20the%20charts%20below%20show%20both%20earnings%20growth%20estimates%20for%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20and%20the%20rate%20of%20change%20of%20those%20estimates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222686%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22earnings%20upgrades%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69cea378c02a678bd7e4766a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221052%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESociete%20Generale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20see%20loads%20of%20commentary%20talking%20about%20buoyant%20US%20profits%20upgrades.%20By%20contrast%20I%20have%20seen%20only%20one%20comment%20(and%20believe%20you%20me%20I%20look%20at%20a%20lot%20of%20stuff)%20that%20concurs%20with%20my%20contention%20that%20profits%20momentum%20has%20begun%20to%20stall%2C%26quot%3B%20Edwards%20wrote%2C%20the%20emphasis%20his.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20second%20derivative%20that%20matters%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESlower-growing%20but%20still-positive%20analyst%20optimism%20might%20seem%20benign%2C%20but%20Edwards%20warned%20that%20the%20slowdown%20could%20signal%20that%20the%20earnings%20picture%20is%20starting%20to%20sour%20as%20investors%20come%20to%20grips%20with%20the%20inflationary%20and%20anti-growth%20implications%20of%20higher%20oil%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigher%20inflation%20levels%20tend%20to%20push%20up%20longer-term%20interest%20rates%20as%20investors%20seek%20greater%20compensation.%20They%20also%20mean%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20more%20likely%20to%20hike%20short-term%20interest%20rates%20to%20cool%20off%20an%20economy.%20Both%20have%20historically%20weighed%20on%20stock%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20surge%20in%20oil%20prices%20seems%20to%20have%20foiled%20investors'%20hopes%20for%20additional%20Federal%20Reserve%20rate%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20economists%20worry%20that%20high%20oil%20prices%20could%20eat%20into%20consumers'%20budgets%2C%20hurting%20growth.%20It's%20a%20recipe%20for%20disaster%20for%20investors%3A%20stagflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20market%20pros%20think%20it's%20too%20early%20to%20fear%20such%20a%20scenario.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20talking%20about%20war%20efforts%20that%20go%20on%20for%20years%20and%20years%20that%20plant%20the%20seeds%20of%20stagflation%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-why-buy-the-dip-now-iran-war-sp500-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJeff%20Weniger%2C%20the%20head%20of%20equity%20strategy%20at%20WisdomTree%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20earlier%20this%20week.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20one%20month%20into%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-stocks-today-trump-iran-war-oil-prices-wall-street-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStocks%20rallied%20furiously%20on%20Tuesday%20and%20Wednesday%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20week%20on%20prospects%20of%20de-escalation%20in%20Iran%20and%20a%20potential%20reopening%20of%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20though%2C%20Edwards%20is%20skeptical%20of%20the%20timely%20resolution%20investors%20are%20hoping%20for.%20Even%20if%20the%20US%20pulls%20out%20of%20the%20conflict%2C%20the%20possibility%20remains%20that%20Israel%20could%20continue%20strikes%20on%20Iran%2C%20he%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20commentators%20and%20investors%20appear%20to%20not%20expect%20this%20war%20to%20wreak%20the%20economic%20havoc%20some%20of%20us%20still%20remember%20from%20the%201970s%2C%26quot%3B%20Edwards%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThat%20smacks%20of%20complacency%20to%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-earnings-growth-sp500-iran-war-oil-prices-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1775209501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ce7ec56a864f6fcd7bcb75%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-earnings-growth-sp500-iran-war-oil-prices-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BThe%20equity%20market%20may%20be%20looking%20in%20the%20rear-view%20earnings%20mirror%20and%20taking%20comfort%20from%20such%20robust%20profits%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Albert%20Edwards.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22wedwards%40businessinsider.com%20(William%20Edwards)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-earnings-growth-sp500-iran-war-oil-prices-2026-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20used%20to%20advise%20companies%20on%20what%20to%20pay%20people.%20Here%20are%204%20myths%20you%20should%20ignore%20when%20negotiating%20your%20salary.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221505%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gerta%20Malaj%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69cc25dce762ed6cfe448fa8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221129%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGerta%20Malaj%20used%20to%20help%20companies%20determine%20employee%20compensation.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Gerta%20Malaj%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGerta%20Malaj%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-coach-shares-simple-salary-negotiation-phrase-2026-3%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enegotiation%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20guides%20executives%20and%20mid-career%20professionals.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMalaj%20previously%20worked%20at%20Salary.com%2C%20where%20she%20helped%20firms%20determine%20employee%20compensation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20warns%20against%20following%20common%20advice%2C%20like%20relying%20too%20much%20on%20market%20research%20or%20playing%20hard%20to%20get.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Gerta%20Malaj%2C%20who%20used%20to%20work%20at%20Salary.com%20and%20LinkedIn.%20She's%20now%20the%20cofounder%20of%20YourNegotiations.com.%20Her%20employment%20and%20identity%20have%20been%20verified%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20negotiation%20advisor%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20cofounded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyournegotiations.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYournegotiations.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20help%20executives%20and%20mid-career%20professionals%20negotiate%20job%20offers%20and%20business%20deals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20credit%20my%20negotiation%20expertise%20to%20a%20few%20things.%20First%2C%20I'm%20from%20Albania%2C%20which%20is%20a%20developing%20country.%20I%20had%20to%20navigate%20constrained%20resources%20my%20whole%20life.%20Second%2C%20I%20have%20a%20passion%20for%20behavioral%20science%20and%20psychology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20I%20worked%20at%20Salary.com%2C%20where%20I%20advised%20companies%20on%20how%20to%20pay%20their%20employees.%20All%20of%20that%20experience%20has%20given%20me%20some%20hot%20takes%20on%20negotiations.%20Here%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnegotiation-coach-shares-salary-discussion-mistakes-to-avoid-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efour%20common%20myths%20to%20disregard%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20negotiating%20your%20salary%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d76dc5c2-c6c0-4bf4-8602-874f090b6d77%5C%22%3ERely%20on%20market%20research%20to%20figure%20out%20your%20salary%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20at%20Salary.com%20and%20we%20had%20hundreds%20and%20thousands%20of%20data%20points%20filtered%20by%20industry%2C%20location%2C%20and%20company%20size.%20Those%20are%20three%20key%20variables%20that%20inform%20a%20company%20on%20how%20to%20pay%20someone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20would%20pay%20us%20to%20present%20that%20data%20and%20tell%20them%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-coach-shares-simple-salary-negotiation-phrase-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emuch%20they%20should%20pay%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20ultimately%2C%20many%20of%20them%20would%20go%20in%20a%20different%20direction%20than%20what%20we%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20spending%20hours%20doing%20research%20on%20what%20companies%20are%20paying%20their%20employees%2C%20you're%20wasting%20your%20time.%20It%20often%20doesn't%20matter%20what%20other%20companies%20are%20paying%20because%20each%20firm%20has%20their%20own%20philosophy%2C%20and%20each%20team%20has%20their%20own%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20thing%20people%20can%20do%20for%20themselves%20is%20get%20another%20offer%20to%20understand%20their%20market%20value.%20I%20recommend%20not%20having%20a%20number%20in%20mind.%20Even%20market%20data%20isn't%20one%20number%2C%20it's%20a%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENegotiations%20are%20like%20playing%20cards%20%E2%80%94%20and%20conducting%20market%20research%20is%20like%20trying%20to%20look%20at%20the%20person's%20cards.%20You%20can%20never%20know%20the%20cards%20someone%20is%20holding.%20The%20best%20you%20can%20do%20is%20play%20your%20hand%20as%20well%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2245d339d2-1d34-4851-98d8-195d43c5852d%5C%22%3EGive%20a%20salary%20number%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recommend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-people-make-negotiating-job-offer-from-salary-negotiator-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enever%20giving%20a%20prospective%20employer%20a%20salary%20number%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20very%20few%20exceptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20role%20has%20its%20own%20budget%20that%20is%20informed%20beyond%20just%20the%20market%20data.%20It's%20informed%20by%20internal%20variables%2C%20like%20what%20budget%20they%20were%20approved%20for%2C%20if%20they're%20raising%20funding%20soon%2C%20or%20if%20someone%20critical%20has%20left%20and%20the%20company%20needs%20to%20fill%20the%20position%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20can%20never%20really%20know%20a%20company's%20budget%20for%20a%20given%20role.%20So%20when%20you%20give%20a%20number%20and%20they%20accept%20it%2C%20you%20never%20know%20if%20there's%20money%20left%20on%20the%20table.%20If%20you%20overshoot%20above%20the%20budget%2C%20they%20may%20think%20you're%20entitled%20or%20that%20you%20won't%20be%20happy%20there%20with%20what%20they%20can%20give%20you%20and%20they%20might%20not%20take%20you%20to%20the%20final%20offer%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20exception%20is%20if%20you%20already%20negotiated%20with%20the%20company%20and%20they%20didn't%20budge%2C%20and%20you%20have%20a%20better%20offer%20from%20somewhere%20else.%20However%2C%20you%20never%20want%20to%20lie%20about%20having%20another%20offer%20because%20recruiters%20can%20pick%20up%20on%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethis.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EYou%20also%20have%20to%20come%20up%20with%20a%20whole%20universe%20of%20lies%20and%20remember%20every%20detail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22581e9169-963c-4b6c-801c-636bf857e760%5C%22%3EPlay%20it%20cool%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20get%20clients%20who%20play%20hard%20to%20get%2C%20but%20that's%20actually%20the%20wrong%20move.%20When%20you%20interview%2C%20you%20actually%20want%20to%20show%20a%20lot%20of%20excitement%2C%20because%20that%20will%20offset%20the%20negotiation.%20That%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20should%20say%20%26quot%3Byes%26quot%3B%20immediately.%20The%20other%20party%20would%20rather%20you%20say%20%26quot%3Byes%26quot%3B%20and%20be%20done%20with%20it.%20But%20if%20you%20show%20a%20lot%20of%20excitement%2C%20you're%20offsetting%20the%20work%20you%20create%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20people%20want%20to%20work%20with%20people%20who%20want%20to%20be%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22002c76c0-83e6-4350-bcd1-ee3f040d38cc%5C%22%3EOver-communicate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver-communicating%20is%20the%20one%20quality%20that%20makes%20someone%20an%20amazing%20employee%2C%20but%20a%20bad%20negotiator.%20That%20may%20include%20sharing%20that%20you%20want%20to%20take%20a%20sabbatical%2C%20have%20kids%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewant%20to%20start%20your%20own%20company%2C%20or%20even%20talking%20about%20other%20interviews%20you've%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20may%20want%20to%20over-communicate%20because%20there%20are%20stakeholders%20and%20you%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20everyone's%20aligned.%20But%20that%20can%20really%20can%20hurt%20you%2C%20because%20everything%20you%20say%20can%20be%20used%20against%20you.%20So%20you%20want%20to%20actually%20keep%20your%20heart%20close%20to%20your%20chest%20and%20not%20overshare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalary-consultant-warns-against-common-negotiation-myths-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1775209381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69cc25dce762ed6cfe448fa8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalary-consultant-warns-against-common-negotiation-myths-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gerta%20Malaj%20used%20to%20advise%20firms%20on%20what%20to%20pay%20employees.%20She%20warns%20against%20following%20common%20advice%2C%20like%20doing%20too%20much%20market%20research.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalary-consultant-warns-against-common-negotiation-myths-2026-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prevent%20Him%20From%20Speaking%20Wrong%3A%20BJP%20Slams%20AAP%20Over%20Raghav%20Chadha's%20Demotion%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22When%20asked%20about%20buzz%20that%20the%20AAP%20leader%20ma