%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ce7012e762ed6cfe449939%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223212%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEddy%20Cue%20oversees%20Apple's%20services%20department.%3Cp%3EBryn%20Lennon%20-%20Formula%201%2FFormula%201%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EEddy%20Cue%20reflected%20on%20how%20iTunes%20revolutionized%20Apple's%20service%20strategy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20iTunes%20Store's%20success%20was%20a%20precursor%20to%20Apple's%20services%20business%20reaching%20new%20heights.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EApple's%20pricing%20strategy%20for%20iTunes%20helped%20it%20overcome%20challenges%20from%20music%20piracy%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fitunes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EiTunes%20Store%3C%2Fa%3E%20reshaped%20Apple%20and%20the%20music%20industry%2C%20laying%20the%20groundwork%20for%20its%20booming%20services%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEddy%20Cue%2C%20the%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20services%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EApple%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20joined%20daily%20tech%20talk%20show%20TBPN%20on%20Wednesday%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20look%20back%20on%20his%2038%20years%20at%20the%20company.%20Cue%20oversees%20Apple's%20services%2C%20including%20its%20subscription-based%20platforms%20Apple%20Music%20and%20Apple%20TV%2C%20among%20others.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20there%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-music%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EApple%20Music%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20was%20the%20iTunes%20Store%2C%20which%20started%20out%20selling%20songs%20and%20albums.%20Cue%20said%20it%20was%20a%20real%20game%20changer%20for%20Apple%20when%20it%20launched%20in%202003.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20truly%20revolutionized%20music%2C%20and%20it%20really%20gave%20us%20a%20whole%20different%20perspective%20of%20what%20services%20can%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Cue%20told%20hosts%20Jordi%20Hays%20and%20John%20Coogan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20glimpse%20of%20what%20would%20make%20up%20Apple's%20modern%20ecosystem%20%E2%80%94%20the%20combination%20of%20hardware%20and%20software%2C%20with%20services%20added.%20However%2C%20it%20took%20some%20convincing%20to%20make%20it%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnapster-making-comeback-metaverse-music-platform-millennials-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20era%20of%20Napster%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20music%20piracy%2C%20major%20record%20labels%20weren't%20sure%20it%20was%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20let%20Apple%20sell%20songs%20for%20%240.99.%20They%20wanted%20to%20build%20their%20own%20platforms%2C%20Cue%20said.%20Apple%20warned%20that%20wouldn't%20work%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20had%20different%20pricing%20for%20each%20song.%20They%20had%20different%20rules%2C%26quot%3B%20Cue%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20all%20over%20the%20map.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Apple's%20strategy%20relied%20on%20consistent%20pricing%20and%20an%20open%20transaction%20system%20that%20would%20allow%20users%20to%20buy%20multiple%20songs%20over%20time%2C%20rather%20than%20buying%20them%20piecemeal.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20customer%20could%20buy%20multiple%20songs%20in%20a%2024-hour%20period%20and%20be%20charged%20for%20them%20in%20a%20single%20transaction%2C%20to%20avoid%20additional%20credit%20card%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20closing%20the%20transaction%20on%20every%20single%20one%2C%20why%20don't%20we%20just%20combine%20them%20over%20a%20period%20of%20time%3F%20Let's%20keep%20the%20transaction%20open%2C%26quot%3B%20Cue%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20worked%20out%2C%20Cue%20said%2C%20as%20most%20transactions%20were%20worth%20more%20than%20%240.99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20ultimately%20helped%20the%20then%20%26quot%3Bcratering%26quot%3B%20music%20business%2C%20Cue%20said.%20He%20said%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-jobs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecofounder%20Steve%20Jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20asked%20what%20a%20successful%20launch%20looks%20like%20in%20the%20music%20business%2C%20record%20labels%20told%20Cue%20they%20aimed%20to%20sell%201%20million%20songs%20in%20the%20first%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20sold%20a%20million%20songs%20in%20the%20first%20six%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20Cue%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20success%20of%20iTunes%20laid%20the%20foundation%20for%20the%20services%20department%20to%20thrive.%20It%20demonstrated%20how%20Apple%20could%20connect%20more%20directly%20with%20users%20and%20make%20money%20from%20it.%20That%20business%20has%20grown%20exponentially%20under%20CEO%20Tim%20Cook.%20The%20segment%2C%20while%20still%20smaller%20than%20Apple's%20products%20business%2C%20has%20been%20growing%20faster%20with%20%24109%20billion%20in%20revenue%20in%202025%2C%20up%2014%25%20year%20over%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20surpassed%20even%20our%20expectations%2C%20but%20it%20was%20an%20example%20of%20if%20you%20give%20people%20the%20right%20way%2C%20people%20are%20willing%20to%20pay%2C%20but%20it%20has%20to%20be%20done%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Cue%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20iTunes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-eddy-cue-explains-how-itunes-shaped-its-services-strategy-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1775208721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ce70206a864f6fcd7bcaf3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-eddy-cue-explains-how-itunes-shaped-its-services-strategy-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Apple's%20SVP%20Eddy%20Cue%20reflected%20on%20the%20iTunes%20Store's%20launch%20and%20its%20revolutionary%20impact%20on%20the%20music%20industry%20and%20Apple's%