ey%20calculated%20their%20'FIRE%20number'%20and%20saved%20up%20to%2070%25%20of%20their%20income%20without%20feeling%20deprived%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kristy%20Shen%20and%20Bryce%20Leung%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ce99ea6a864f6fcd7bcc5b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKristy%20Shen%20and%20Bryce%20Leung%20are%20early%20retirees%20and%20the%20founders%20of%20The%20Millennial%20Revolution.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kristy%20Shen%20and%20Bryce%20Leung%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKristy%20Shen%20and%20Bryce%20Leung%20kept%20their%20savings%20in%20a%20bank%20account%20for%20years%2C%20planning%20to%20buy%20a%20home.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20home%20prices%20kept%20going%20up%2C%20they%20grew%20frustrated%20and%20redirected%20their%20savings%20into%20index%20funds.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThanks%20to%20aggressive%20saving%2C%20they%20built%20a%20seven-figure%20portfolio%20and%20quit%20their%20jobs%20in%20their%2030s.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Kristy%20Shen%20first%20heard%20about%20the%20financial%20independence%2C%20retire%20early%20(FIRE)%20movement%2C%20she%20thought%20it%20sounded%20like%20a%20scam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%202010s%2C%20the%20FIRE%20community%20was%20still%20small%2C%20with%20bloggers%20like%20Mr.%20Money%20Mustache%20and%20J.L.%20Collins%20leading%20the%20conversation%20around%20the%204%25%20rule%20and%20the%20idea%20that%20saving%2025%20times%20your%20annual%20expenses%20could%20lead%20to%20financial%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20I%20grew%20up%20in%20poverty%20in%20China%2C%20my%20thinking%20was%2C%20'The%20stock%20market%20is%20scary%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Shen%2C%20whose%20family%20moved%20to%20Canada%20when%20she%20was%20eight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20understanding%20of%20money%20was%20largely%20shaped%20by%20her%20parents'%20advice%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20and%20avoid%20the%20market.%20Meanwhile%2C%20FIRE%20bloggers%20were%20claiming%20you%20could%20retire%20in%20your%2030s%20by%20utilizing%20index%20fund%20investing.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20really%20believe%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20Shen%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20Bryce%20Leung%2C%20were%20focused%20on%20saving%20for%20a%20home.%20The%20couple%2C%20who%20met%20while%20studying%20computer%20engineering%2C%20were%20both%20working%20in%20tech%20and%20earning%20good%20salaries.%20But%20homeownership%20in%20Toronto%20still%20felt%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHousing%20prices%20would%20just%20go%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Shen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20frustration%20with%20the%20housing%20market%20pushed%20them%20to%20consider%20other%20options%20and%20ultimately%20led%20them%20to%20the%20FIRE%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222831%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kristy%20Shen%20Bryce%20Leung%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ce9d0ac02a678bd7e47626%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222123%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShen%20and%20Leung%20have%20spent%20years%20traveling%20the%20world%20on%20%2440%2C000%20CAD%20per%20year.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kristy%20Shen%20Bryce%20Leung%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22943cd517-3c77-4951-bf27-8e7d0726ebec%5C%22%3ECalculating%20their%20FIRE%20number%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20retirement%20sounded%20appealing%2C%20but%20it%20was%20economic%20uncertainty%20that%20motivated%20them%20to%20come%20up%20with%20a%20backup%20plan%2C%20Leung%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BFIRE%20seemed%20to%20be%20a%20way%20for%20us%20to%20kind%20of%20insulate%20ourselves%20from%20what%20were%20the%20threats%20to%20job%20stability%2C%20which%20back%20then%20was%20outsourcing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20used%20the%204%25%20rule%2C%20a%20common%20FIRE%20guideline%20that%20says%20you%20can%20withdraw%20about%204%25%20of%20your%20portfolio%20each%20year%20in%20retirement.%20That%20means%20you%20need%20roughly%2025%20times%20your%20annual%20expenses%20invested.%20They%20were%20spending%20about%20%2440%2C000%20CAD%20a%20year%2C%20putting%20their%20FIRE%20number%20at%20%241%20million%20CAD%20(25%20times%20%2440%2C0000).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20expected%20it%20would%20take%20five%20to%2010%20years%20to%20hit%20seven%20figures.%20Instead%2C%20they%20got%20there%20in%20just%20a%20few.%20They%20had%20a%20significant%20head%20start%3A%20By%202012%2C%20when%20they%20first%20discovered%20the%20online%20FIRE%20community%2C%20the%20couple%20said%20they%20had%20already%20saved%20about%20%24500%2C000%20CAD%20for%20a%20down%20payment.%20They%20simply%20changed%20the%20goal%20for%20that%20money.%20Rather%20than%20use%20it%20to%20buy%20a%20home%2C%20they%20redirected%20the%20money%20into%20low-cost%20index%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2228484c99-9625-42f8-ae5f-b73730ac281c%5C%22%3EHow%20they%20saved%20up%20to%2070%25%20of%20their%20income%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20getting%20serious%20about%20FIRE%2C%20the%20couple%20said%20they%20were%20saving%20roughly%2030%25%20to%2050%25%20of%20their%20income%2C%20which%20peaked%20at%20around%20%24160%2C000%20CAD%20combined.%20Eventually%2C%20they%20pushed%20their%20savings%20rate%20to%2070%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20part%20of%20that%20came%20from%20avoiding%20lifestyle%20creep.%20The%20couple%20stayed%20in%20a%20modest%20one-bedroom%20apartment%2C%20and%20their%20rent%20remained%20about%20the%20same%20for%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20getting%20multiple%20promotions%2C%20we%20did%20not%20increase%20our%20lifestyle%20whatsoever%2C%26quot%3B%20Shen%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20only%20thing%20we%20actually%20did%20spend%20on%2C%20and%20we%20were%20happily%20spending%20on%2C%20was%20travel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20estimated%20they%20spent%20%245%2C000%20to%20%2410%2C000%20a%20year%20on%20travel%2C%20which%20they%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bnon-negotiable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22kristy%20shen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ce9deac02a678bd7e4763a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShen%20and%20Leung%20refused%20to%20give%20up%20their%20travel%20budget%20when%20pursuing%20FIRE.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kristy%20Shen%20and%20Bryce%20Leung%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20to%20saving%20aggressively%20and%20consistently%20is%20not%20to%20deprive%20yourself%20completely%2C%20Leung%20said%2C%20comparing%20cutting%20spending%20to%20dieting%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20do%20it%20for%20a%20little%20while%2C%20but%20then%20eventually%2C%20you%20have%20a%20relapse%2C%20and%20you%20eat%20an%20entire%20birthday%20cake.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20FIRE%20is%20about%20directing%20money%20toward%20what%20matters%20to%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20helps%20to%20keep%20the%20%26quot%3Bbig%20three%26quot%3B%20expenses%20%E2%80%94%20housing%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20food%20%E2%80%94%20in%20check%2C%20which%20they%20did%20by%20renting%20a%20modest%20apartment%2C%20avoiding%20car%20ownership%2C%20and%20cooking%20at%20home.%20That%20freed%20up%20space%20to%20spend%20on%20what%20they%20cared%20about%20most%2C%20travel%2C%20while%20still%20hitting%20their%20savings%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20common%20misconception%20about%20the%20FIRE%20movement%20is%20that%20it%20requires%20deprivation%2C%20Shen%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20it's%20about%20optimization%2C%20not%20minimization.%26quot%3B%20Tracking%20spending%20helped%20them%20do%20that.%20Once%20they%20started%20looking%20closely%20at%20where%20their%20money%20was%20going%2C%20it%20became%20easier%20to%20identify%20what%20added%20value%20and%20what%20didn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20realize%20how%20much%20money%20you're%20actually%20wasting%20on%20things%20you%20barely%20use%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228c2d7bef-63c3-4c27-82eb-d1b3349916c6%5C%22%3EInvesting%20their%20way%20to%20%241%20million%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20savings%20had%20originally%20been%20sitting%20in%20a%20bank%20account%20while%20they%20planned%20to%20buy%20a%20house.%20Once%20they%20committed%20to%20FIRE%2C%20they%20shifted%20their%20money%20into%20a%20diversified%20portfolio%20of%20low-cost%20index%20funds%2C%20including%20VTI%2C%20IEFA%2C%20and%20ZCN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20took%20full%20advantage%20of%20tax-advantaged%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnytime%20that%20you%20have%20an%20opportunity%20to%20get%20free%20money%20or%20tax-advantaged%20money%2C%20you%20definitely%20want%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Leung%2C%20pointing%20to%20accounts%20like%20401(k)s%2C%20Roth%20IRAs%2C%20HSAs%2C%20and%20529%20plans.%20%26quot%3BThe%20less%20money%20you%20give%20to%20the%20government%2C%20the%20more%20money%20you%20have%20for%20yourself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20hitting%20their%20FIRE%20number%20in%202015%2C%20Shen%20and%20Leung%20quit%20their%20jobs%20at%2031%20and%2032%20and%20began%20traveling%20the%20world.%20They've%20been%20living%20off%20their%20portfolio%20ever%20since.%20They've%20earned%20some%20income%20from%20their%20two%20bestselling%20books%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3Fh%3Db9af27a2ecd52de10513d7b1e7d989b87b40170f76cf740cd04339dd102a9624%26postID%3D69ce97f42b9f980b65417292%26postSlug%3Dhow-one-couple-retired-early-financial-independence-savings-investing-strategies-2026-4%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fgp%252Fproduct%252F0525538690%252Fref%253Das_li_tl%253Fie%253DUTF8%2526amp%253Bcamp%253D1789%2526amp%253Bcreative%253D9325%2526amp%253BcreativeASIN%253D0525538690%2526amp%253BlinkCode%253Das2%2526amp%253Btag%253Dkrisandbryc-20%2526amp%253BlinkId%253D7c02632b8a1e2f89f9193b873a48a94f%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EQuit%20Like%20a%20Millionaire%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3Fh%3Dabdc276306fb176c09fa205546d587d89689a8a192272ef03e15e6911062aadf%26postID%3D69ce97f42b9f980b65417292%26postSlug%3Dhow-one-couple-retired-early-financial-independence-savings-investing-strategies-2026-4%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fgp%252Fproduct%252F0593719077%253F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParent%20Like%20a%20Millionaire%20(Without%20Being%20One)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20said%20they%20don't%20rely%20on%20those%20earnings%20to%20sustain%20their%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20screenshots%20of%20their%20investment%20portfolio%20reviewed%20by%20BI%2C%20they've%20more%20than%20doubled%20their%20net%20worth%20since%20retiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20couple%2C%20FIRE%20ultimately%20became%20less%20about%20early%20retirement%20and%20more%20about%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20FIRE%20thing%20is%20really%20nice%2C%20but%20what's%20actually%20really%20important%20is%20why%20you%20are%20getting%20to%20that%20number%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20Shen%20said.%20That%20became%20especially%20clear%20during%20a%20family%20emergency%2C%20when%20they%20flew%20back%20to%20help%20care%20for%20Leung's%20father%20after%20he%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20brain%20cancer.%20%26quot%3BWe%20realized%2C%20OK%2C%20this%20is%20what%20FI%20is%20for.%20You%20buy%20your%20time%20back%20so%20that%20you%20can%20be%20there%20for%20the%20people%20that%20you%20love.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20financial%20independence%20also%20gave%20them%20more%20freedom%20as%20parents%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20actually%20be%20present%2C%20spend%20time%20with%20them%2C%20and%20not%20miss%20out%20on%20any%20of%20their%20milestones.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReaching%20FI%20was%20never%20just%20about%20walking%20away%20from%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20about%20deprivation.%20It's%20not%20about%20quitting%20your%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20is%20about%20giving%20you%20options.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-one-couple-retired-early-financial-independence-savings-investing-strategies-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1775208301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ce99ea6a864f6fcd7bcc5b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-one-couple-retired-early-financial-independence-savings-investing-strategies-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20hitting%20their%20FIRE%20number%20in%202015%2C%20one%20couple%20quit%20their%20jobs%20to%20travel%20the%20world.%20They've%20been%20living%20off%20their%20portfolio%20ever%20since.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-one-couple-retired-early-financial-independence-savings-investing-strategies-2026-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Ghar%20wapsi%20soon'%3A%20Imam%20chief's%20prediction%20on%20PoK%2C%20praises%20'new%20Kashmir'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1775208232000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-129998029%2Cimgsize-633809.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fghar-wapsi-will-take-place-soon-all-india-imam-organisation-chief-says-pok-will-be-reintegrated-with-india%2Farticleshow%2F129997987.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chief%20Imam%20Umer%20Ahmed%20Ilyasi%20expressed%20confidence%20that%20Pakistan-Occupied%20Kashmir%20will%20soon%20rejoin%20India%2C%20citing%20the%20desire%20of%20its%20people%20and%20the%20positive%20developments%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20post-Article%20370%20abrogation.%20He%20highlighted%20a%20transformed%20Kashmir%20with%20increased%20prosperity%20and%20tourism%2C%20urging%20continued%20visits%20despite%20past%20incidents.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fghar-wapsi-will-take-place-soon-all-india-imam-organisation-chief-says-pok-will-be-reintegrated-with-india%2Farticleshow%2F129997987.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Wall%20Street%20tries%20to%20keep%20junior%20hours%20in%20check%2C%20from%20weekly%20guidelines%20to%20'pencils%20down'%20periods%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22David%20Solomon%2C%20Jamie%20Dimon%2C%20Jane%20Fraser%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69cd4d40e762ed6cfe449457%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDavid%20Solomon%2C%20Jamie%20Dimon%2C%20and%20Jane%20Fraser's%20banks%20all%20have%20policies%20in%20place%20to%20monitor%20bankers'%20hours.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWall%20Street%20firms%20have%20a%20range%20of%20policies%20to%20monitor%20junior%20bankers'%20notoriously%20long%20hours.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20first%20quarter%20of%202026%20saw%20record%20M%26amp%3BA%20volume%2C%20which%20could%20push%20up%20hours.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20how%20banks%2C%20from%20JPMorgan%20to%20Citi%2C%20try%20to%20keep%20tabs%20on%20how%20much%20juniors%20are%20working.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJPMorgan%20CEO%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EJamie%20Dimon%20has%20said%20that%20people%20will%20probably%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjamie-dimon-jpmorgan-ai-work-jobs-life-skills-cancer-healthcare-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworking%203.5%20days%20a%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20a%20few%20decades%2C%20but%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20many%20of%20his%20own%20bankers%20are%20still%20logged%20on%20far%20more%20than%20the%20typical%2040%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJunior%20bankers%2C%20known%20as%20analysts%20and%20associates%2C%20work%20notoriously%20grueling%20hours%20across%20firms%2C%20which%20have%20come%20under%20renewed%20scrutiny%20in%20recent%20years.%20(A%20boutique%20bank%2C%20Centerview%20Partners%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjunior-bankers-work-hours-shiber-centerview-wall-street-lawsuit-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enarrowly%20evaded%20a%20trial%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20February%20that%20would%20have%20put%20analysts'%20hours%20on%20the%20witness%20stand.)%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeal%20volume%20in%202026%20suggests%20that%20bankers%20will%20have%20a%20lot%20to%20keep%20them%20busy%20this%20year%3A%20M%26amp%3BA%20volume%20topped%20%241.2%20trillion%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%2C%20thanks%20to%20a%20slate%20of%20megadeals%2C%20according%20to%20LSEG%20data.%20Though%20the%20number%20of%20deals%20fell%20year%20over%20year%2C%20deal%20volume%20jumped%2026%25%2C%20according%20to%20the%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecord%20dealmaking%20is%20part%20of%20what%20sparked%20conversations%20about%20working%20hours%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20Concern%20spiked%20again%20after%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-transfixed-by-bofa-banker-leo-lukenas-untimely-death-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ELeo%20Lukenas%20III%2C%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ea%2035-year-old%20investment%20banking%20associate%20at%20Bank%20of%20America%20who%20had%20helped%20close%20a%20%242%20billion%20acquisition%2C%20died%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20some%20banks%20introduced%20new%20policies%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20and%20have%20continued%20to%20tweak%20them%20as%20recently%20as%20last%20month%20%E2%80%94%20juniors'%20hours%20may%20not%20have%20changed%20much.%20Data%20from%20recruiting%20firm%20Odyssey%20Search%20Partners%20found%20that%20junior%20bankers%20worked%20as%20much%20in%202025%20as%20in%202022%2C%20the%20last%20time%20the%20survey%20of%20300%20first-%20and%20second-year%20analysts%20went%20out.%20Those%20working%20at%20bulge-bracket%20banks%20reported%20an%20average%20of%2081%20hours%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrianne%20Sterling%2C%20the%20head%20of%20investment%20banking%20at%20the%20recruiting%20firm%20Selby%20Jennings%2C%20said%20juniors'%20hours%20haven't%20changed%20meaningfully%2C%20but%20that%20young%20employees%20are%20working%20on%20more%20live%20deals%2C%20which%20tends%20to%20make%20the%20job%20more%20exciting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20hearing%20people%20working%20a%20lot%20of%20hours%2C%20but%20we're%20not%20hearing%20tons%20and%20tons%20of%20bankers%20complaining%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20banks%20have%20guidelines%20for%20weekly%20hours%20or%20%26quot%3Bpencils%20down%26quot%3B%20periods%20when%20juniors%20aren't%20expected%20to%20work.%20Still%2C%20Sterling%20said%20they%20often%20aren't%20effective%2C%20since%20they%20include%20carve-outs%20when%20bankers%20and%20clients%20are%20negotiating%20transactions%20in%20real%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20if%20there's%20a%20client%20demand%2C%20the%20client%20demand%20does%20come%20before%20anything%20else.%20When%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20live%20deals%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20whoever's%20in%20charge%20of%20Baker%20hours%20probably%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20those%20override%20requests%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Sterling%20thinks%20that%20banks%20have%20become%20more%20conscious%20of%20retaining%20bankers%20beyond%20their%20two-year%20analyst%20rotations%20and%20taking%20care%20of%20staff.%20Most%20young%20bankers%2C%20she%20said%2C%20also%20know%20what%20the%20hours%20will%20be%20when%20accepting%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-banks-ai-strategy-jpmorgan-goldman-citi-bofa-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efirms%20have%20introduced%20AI%20%3C%2Fa%3Einto%20bankers'%20workflows%2C%20Jennings%20said%20she%20hasn't%20yet%20heard%20that%20the%20technology%20is%20transforming%20the%20number%20of%20hours%20employees%20work.%20Some%2C%20however%2C%20have%20told%20her%20that%20they%20hope%20AI%20can%20eventually%20reduce%20hours%2C%20or%20at%20least%20hours%20spent%20on%20menial%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20some%20of%20Wall%20Street's%20biggest%20banks%20monitor%20their%20junior%20employees'%20hours%2C%20from%20protected%20weekends%20to%20electronic%20tracking%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225aa43515-db07-4157-a468-f19956eb9ced%5C%22%3EJPMorgan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20JPMorgan%20piloted%20a%20new%20tool%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-objectives-software-engineers-developers-boost-productivity-ai-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eelectronically%20track%3C%2Fa%3E%20junior%20bankers'%20hours%2C%20which%20will%20soon%20be%20rolled%20out%20to%20the%20broader%20population.%20The%20estimate%20is%20based%20on%20digital%20activity%2C%20like%20scheduled%20meetings%2C%20Zoom%20calls%2C%20and%20desktop%20use%2C%20and%20will%20serve%20as%20a%20point%20of%20comparison%20for%20the%20hours%20juniors%20log%20manually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMuch%20like%20the%20weekly%20screen%20time%20summaries%20on%20a%20smartphone%2C%20this%20tool%20is%20about%20awareness%E2%80%94not%20enforcement.%20It's%20designed%20to%20support%20transparency%2C%20well-being%2C%20and%20encourage%20open%20conversations%20about%20workload%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesman%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nation's%20largest%20bank%20uses%20an%2080-hour%20weekly%20workload%20guideline%20for%20junior%20bankers%2C%20with%20exceptions%20for%20certain%20circumstances%2C%20including%20live%20deals.%20Juniors%20get%20one%20full%20protected%20weekend%20off%20every%20three%20months%20and%20protected%20holiday%20long%20weekends.%20They%20also%20have%20a%20mandated%20no-work%20period%20from%206%20pm%20on%20Friday%20to%2012%20pm%20on%20Saturday%2C%20with%20exceptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225fdbdd4f-7f85-4ad5-92a6-0ec22591500a%5C%22%3EBank%20of%20America%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBank%20of%20America%20introduced%20a%20tool%20in%202024%20to%20better%20track%20junior%20bankers'%20weekly%20hours%20and%20flag%20when%20they%20exceed%2080.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20later%2C%20the%20bank%20elevated%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20role%20of%20its%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbofa-leo-lukenis-staffers-cro-junior-bankers-wall-street-burnout-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20chief%20resource%20officers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20oversee%20juniors'%20workloads%20and%20career%20development.%20Under%20the%20new%20structure%2C%20senior%20bankers%20at%20the%20director%20level%20and%20above%20hold%20the%20position%20permanently%2C%20rather%20than%20midlevel%20bankers%2C%20who%20previously%20held%20it%20temporarily.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d952627-f7b7-4728-9e60-b08049b291db%5C%22%3EGoldman%20Sachs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJuniors%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%20aren't%20expected%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20from%209%20pm%20on%20Friday%20to%209%20am%20on%20Sunday%2C%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-ceo-responds-junior-analysts-work-conditions-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20firm's%20%26quot%3BSaturday%20rule%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20part%20of%20the%20effort%20to%20ensure%20they're%20not%20working%20too%20many%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20bank's%20management%20monitors%20junior%20staffing%20and%20activity%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bregularly%20adjusts%20the%20workloads%20of%20our%20teams.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f2659fcd-9c9c-45a7-a8d8-83df544d1aeb%5C%22%3EWells%20Fargo%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwells-fargo-hiring-spree-investment-bankers-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWells%20Fargo%20%3C%2Fa%3Emonitors%20analysts'%20and%20associates'%20weekly%20hours%2C%20which%20team%20leads%20review%20each%20week.%20They%20try%20to%20reassign%20work%20during%20busy%20periods%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20confirmed%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20and%20associates%20are%20expected%20to%20step%20away%20from%20work%20from%20Friday%20evening%20to%20midday%20Saturday%2C%20and%20all%20bankers%20have%20protected%20holiday%20long%20weekends.%20Junior%20employees%20have%20additional%20discretionary%20protected%20weekends%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20continued.%20Any%20exceptions%20to%20the%20weekly%20%26quot%3Bpencils%20down%26quot%3B%20period%20and%20protected%20holidays%20need%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d648c974-2229-47b3-a6de-8d08d3be7338%5C%22%3EMorgan%20Stanley%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdevgen-ai-tool-saved-morgan-stanley-280-000-hours-jobs-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMorgan%20Stanley%3C%2Fa%3E%20monitors%20excess%20workflow%2C%20and%20a%20source%20familiar%20with%20the%20policies%20said%20the%20firm%20continually%20updates%20policies%20to%20address%20any%20situations%20that%20require%20a%20more%20in-depth%20or%20personalized%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aatecotzky%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eatecotzky%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20alicetecotzky.05.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powe