0centers%20as%20it%20accelerates%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20mass%20deportation%20push.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.governor.nh.gov%2Fsites%2Fg%2Ffiles%2Fehbemt971%2Ffiles%2Finline-documents%2Fmerrimack-detention-reengineering-initiative-3.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20plans%20to%20convert%20the%20vacant%20industrial%20warehouses%2C%20which%20were%20originally%20built%20for%20distribution%20and%20logistics%2C%20into%20detention%20centers%20capable%20of%20holding%20thousands%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20confirmed%20the%2011%20warehouse%20purchases%20through%20local%20deed%20searches%20and%20public%20records%20requests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.costar.com%2Farticle%2F1306766767%2Fsellers-cash-in-on-ices-revamp-of-national-detention-center-network%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20real%20estate%20data%20company%20CoStar%20found%20that%20ICE%20paid%20premiums%20of%2011%25%20to%2013%25%20for%20the%20buildings.%20Sale%20prices%20ranged%20from%20%2435%20million%20for%20a%20261%2C000-square-foot%20warehouse%20in%20San%20Antonio%20to%20%24145%20million%20for%20an%20833%2C000-%20square-foot%20warehouse%20in%20Salt%20Lake%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FUBcVr%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20map%20showing%20locations%20of%20warehouses%20purchased%20for%20use%20as%20ICE%20detention%20facilities%2C%20with%20two%20each%20in%20Pennsylvania%2C%20Georgia%2C%20and%20Texas%2C%20and%20one%20each%20in%20Arizona%2C%20Utah%2C%20Michigan%2C%20Maryland%2C%20and%20New%20Jersey.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FUBcVr%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C